AbleCredit Android SDK — Integration & API Documentation
Version: 1.0
Last Updated: October 2025

1. Overview
This document describes how to integrate the AbleCredit Android SDK (SdkManager) and explains each public API method available to integrators. The content below is derived from the SDK source you provided and contains only actual SDK methods.
2. Gradle Plugins & Dependencies
Add these plugins at the top of your module-level Gradle file:

plugins {
    alias(libs.plugins.android.application)
    alias(libs.plugins.kotlin.android)
    id("org.jetbrains.kotlin.kapt")
    id("kotlin-parcelize")
}
Required dependencies (inside `dependencies` block):

// Android core
implementation("androidx.core:core-ktx:1.13.1")
implementation("androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.7.0")
implementation("com.google.android.material:material:1.12.0")

// Room
implementation("androidx.room:room-runtime:2.6.1")
implementation("androidx.room:room-ktx:2.6.1")
kapt("androidx.room:room-compiler:2.6.1")

// Coroutines
implementation("org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.8.1")
implementation("org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.8.1")

// WorkManager, Lifecycle
implementation("androidx.work:work-runtime-ktx:2.9.1")
implementation("androidx.lifecycle:lifecycle-runtime-ktx:2.8.2")
implementation("androidx.lifecycle:lifecycle-viewmodel-ktx:2.8.4")

// Networking
implementation("com.squareup.okhttp3:okhttp:4.12.0")
implementation("com.squareup.okhttp3:logging-interceptor:4.12.0")
implementation("com.squareup.retrofit2:retrofit:2.11.0")
implementation("com.squareup.retrofit2:converter-gson:2.11.0")

// Location
implementation("com.google.android.gms:play-services-location:21.3.0")

// SDK AAR
implementation(files("libs/app-release.aar"))
3. SDK Configuration
The SDK maintains configuration internally. You can read it via:
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.getSdkConfig()
Returns
SdkConfig(apiKey, tenantId, userId, baseUrl)

SdkConfig fields:
Key
Value
apiKey
String? (API key used for authentication)
tenantId
String? (Tenant identifier)
userId
String? (User identifier)
baseUrl
String? (API base URL)

4. initialize()
Purpose: Initializes the SDK with credentials and configuration. Must be called before invoking any other method.
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.initialize(context, apiKey, tenantId, userId, baseUrl, onResult)
Callback
onResult(status: Int, message: String) — status 1 = success, 0 = failure
Behavior
Validates credentials, sets internal config, and prepares repositories.


SdkManager.initialize(
    context = this,
    apiKey = “<api_key>”,
    tenantId = "MUTHOOT-49211173",
    userId = "shwe@gml.co",
    baseUrl = "https://col-api-qa.ablecredit.com/api/v2/"
) { status, message ->
    if (status == 1) {
        // SDK initialized successfully
    } else {
        // Initialization failed
    }
}
5. createNewLoanCase()
Purpose: Creates a new loan application using the repository and network layer.
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.createNewLoanCase(context, payload: LoanRequest, onResult: (LoanResponse?) -> Unit)
Threading
Uses coroutines (Dispatchers.IO → Dispatchers.Main)
On success
Returns LoanResponse and shows a Toast
On failure
Shows Toast 'Failed to create loan' and returns null


LoanRequest(
    loan_reference = "LN-REF-20251017-0008",
    client_unique_id = "CUST-20251017-1234",
    product_id = "MUT-IND-3065",
    branch_id = "ML1348",
    source_system = "hotfoot",
    business_profile = BusinessProfile(
        product = "LAP",
        business_model = "Trading",
        industry = "Fashion Apparel"
    ),
    data = LoanData(
        borrower_details = BorrowerDetails(
            entity_type = "individual",
            name = "Shwetanka Srivastava",
            dob = "24/01/1988",
            mobile = "8197837043"
        )
    )
)
Example call:
SdkManager.createNewLoanCase(this, sampleLoanRequest) { response ->
    // handle response
}
6. recordAudio()
Purpose: Opens RecorderActivity to record audio for a given loan application. Requires SDK initialization and a valid loanApplicationId.
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.recordAudio(context: Context, loanApplicationId: String?)
Navigates to
RecorderActivity (extras: APPLICATION_ID, TITLE)
Behavior
Adds FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK if context is not an Activity; logs call; handles invalid ID.


SdkManager.recordAudio(
    context = this,
    loanApplicationId = "APP-102930"
)
7. capturePhotos()
Purpose: Launches PhotoActivity to capture borrower or document photos. Displays a short Toast when opening the camera.
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.capturePhotos(context: Context, loanApplicationId: String?)
Navigates to
PhotoActivity (extras: APPLICATION_ID, TITLE)
Behavior
Adds FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK for non-Activity contexts; shows Toast.


SdkManager.capturePhotos(
    context = this,
    loanApplicationId = "APP-102930"
)
8. clear()
Purpose: Clears all SDK configuration and resets initialization state. Useful for logout or switching user sessions.
Key
Value
Method
SdkManager.clear(context: Context)
Resets
apiKey, tenantId, userId, baseUrl, initialized = false
Toast
Shows 'SDK cleared successfully'


SdkManager.clear(context = this)
9. Internal helpers (for reference)
`checkInitialization(context)` — ensures SDK initialized; otherwise shows Toast and returns false.
`validateCredentials(apiKey, tenantId, userId)` — currently dummy; replace with real API validation if needed.
10. Notes & Integration Tips
• Always call `initialize()` before invoking SDK features.
• Use `clear()` during logout or when switching tenants.
• Ensure your app requests CAMERA and RECORD_AUDIO permissions.
• Keep `app-release.aar` in `app/libs/` and reference it properly.
• SDK uses Retrofit & OkHttp internally for networking.